&quot;33 pounds of twisted steel and sex appeal.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ukrakajax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraka Jax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/2/02 6:31:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Smokin</span><hr size=1> My opinion is that the developers were passing the pipe around when they &quot;balanced&quot; assassins. Everyone is 100% right that SBs and Nightshades should not get 2.5 spec points without Infiltrators getting some other sort of advantage. The problem is that giving one realm's version of the same class more spec points than the other two was plain stupid to begin with. All other advantages are situational or hard to quantify. Spec points are very visible, and have a large effect on what can be done with a character. SBs and nightshades are very right to want the same number of spec points as infiltrators. Mythic needs to come up with a better way to make the classes &quot;different but equal&quot;. They can start with paying attention to all the good ideas on this board. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ubaym.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Baym</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/3/02 8:00:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3657.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Smokin</span><hr size=1> Kraka is right. There are so many things you are leaving out Tiwgy that are significant differences. First, your 2.5 spec pts mean more than a SB's because they have to spec LA and you don't need to spec DW/CD nearly as high. Infiltrators can be buffed beyond 550AF whereas SB's and NS's cannot except with a realm ability or a charged item. Your weapon choices allow a greater selection of targets than a SB. Your realm abilities are greater than a SBs.<br>
<br>
Kraka is right though. The real crux of the matter is infiltrators should never have been given 2.5 pts to begin with. Unlike many of the infiltrators on this board, I don't believe in nerfing anyone. Since that rules out reducing infiltrators 2.5 specs to something more appropriate, the only equitable solution is to increase all assassins to 2.5.<br>
<br>
